        "timestamp": "2021-10-11 12:03:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nFor policy clamp it seems ok, Liam (we are in spring boot 2.5.0 which requires 5.3.7)\n\nMy 2 cents:\n1. When using spring boot, spring libs should not be overridden except to fix Nexus-IQ issues temporarily.\n2. Not quite sure why spring libs are specified here, and not springboot version ?\nThis will bring more problems than it resolves, I'm even not sure that any Spring lib should be mentioned here as they are really key libs for all projects using them.",
